HEADWORD: Quadruplane
<hw>Quad"ru*plane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>quadru-</ets> in comp. + E. <ets>plane</ets>.]</ety> <def>An
airplane with four superposed main supporting surfaces. Contrasted with
<contr>triplane</contr> <contr>biplane</contr> and
<contr>monoplane</contr>. They are now used only for hobbyist or
historical activities.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

